snippet.textDisplay:
The poet's amazing imagination takes us to the unfortunate night in the Sohni Mahiwal folklore, when Sohni is suffering to meet her beloved Mahiwal. She is trying to convince her claypot to get her to reach the other side of the Chenab river so that she can reunite with Mahiwal, but the claypot is slowly dissolving in the river water and she is about to drown.
The singers, musicians and composers did absolute justice to this beautiful piece of punjabi poetry. Everything about this song is perfect.

'Ghada' is trying to convince Sohni that 'he's' incapable of transporting her to the other side of Chenab and that she shouldn't go, they won't make it.
Then there's a silence and the Sagar veena part comes in and I think that is when Sohni decides to embrace even death if that's what it takes to get to mahiwal.
Involves such powerful inexplicable emotions.
